featured_reviews.review_id:
Have you ever tried to move a family of 4 to Vancouver island? It's extremely stressful. I booked an appointment for our dog to be groomed so she would be out of the house when the movers arrived and the friends she would stay at for 3 days while we moved asked that she be groomed to prevent shedding on their furniture. I woke up on moving day at 6:30 to walk the dog and brush her before her appointment. I showed up on time only to be told the appointment was cancelled because staff called in sick. I wasn't offered any alternative and they wouldn't even let me buy any products in the store because "it was too early" even though I saw a bunch of staff in there. I called all the other grooming shops in the area and they are all full for today. Now I have movers showing up and nowhere to put my dog for the day. It's too hot to leave her in the car. And I can't take her to my friend's house for the next couple of days Because she hasn't been groomed as was asked. I work in the service industry and I understand people call in sick. But sometimes you have to buckle down and make it work. A manager might need to step in and pick up some grooming, shears, or else you need to take five minutes off every appointment in the day in order to squeeze in an extra client or else work a little bit later. I'm very disappointed with the lack of sympathy, lack of effort to rectify their own issue. From now on I'll stick to the little guys. They're cheaper anyway.

** update  I couldn't help but call in and talk to the manager. He was kind and offered another appointment on another day as well as a credit. It didn't help us out the day of and would've been nice if they had offered this during the initial visit.

5 stars for the quality of the care/grooming of my pet

featured_reviews.review_id: I feel very grateful for this Petsmart location for the way they take care of their little critters. I have visited most Petsmarts in the lower mainland and I often saw little hamsters and mice running on wheels that are not only dirty but also way too small for them (it would hurt their spines). And they often lived in smelly cages (pee soaked bedding) and having only pellets (no nutrients) for food. But this Petsmart in North Vancouver provide their rodents with proper size(bigger) and clean wheels to run on, their beddings are clean, and they even give them a variety of fresh vegetables for snacks alongside pellets! I saw happy and healthy  mice exercising on the wheels and comfortably cuddling with each other today. They were so comfortable with humans(thanks to the kind people who take good care of them) they would come out and curiously sniff us. I'm so happy for the animals to be taken such good care of. Thank you guys so much NV Petsmart!

featured_reviews.review_id:
This is the location from which we adopted our beloved cat: Manitoba. The staff were very helpful throughout the adoption process, and the manager (I believe his name was Alex?) went above and beyond. He helped us fill out the paperwork, which because of his help did not feel like a hassle, and he stayed in constant contact throughout the approval and "take home" process. He also waited for us to drive back with our lease agreement documents very close to closing time on a Sunday, and for that we are very grateful. They were working with Action for Animals at the time, and their whole adoption process was very straightforward. Although the profile posted for the public did not go into depth regarding the cats' personalities, they did have folders full of information, advice and recommendations for each of the kitties.
Aside from this, we found the store to be clean and organized, but there were dogs inside barking which made the kittens quite jumpy and scared at times. Also, the cat enclosure did not have a climbing or scratching tower (which most PetSmarts do), so we believe that would be a great addition for the kitties enrichment.

featured_reviews.review_id: Please check the receipt to make sure the price and discount were right before leaving the store. I am an frequent customer. I have been shopping at this store for quite a long time. Last week, I found out a problem at the Main Street  store in North Vancouver. I bought over 20 feeding fishes with my wife and they were on sale. When I paid, a young cashier seems didn't know what kind of fish I bought.  So I told him they were Rosy Red Minnow which was $0.40 each. I also showed him their discount label on my phone.  The discount label said buy 5 save 25% on all fish. The cashier ignored what the label said.  He charged me $0.45 per fish instead of $0.40 per fish.  Then gave me 15% discount but not 25% discount.  Both the charges and discount were not right. My wife told the cashier about the problem and he told us the price he input was correct.  He didn't want to look at my wife and he looked unhappy on what we said from his behavior. Not sure if we are not caucasian. I told my wife to solve the problem later with the Manager. I found the manager and told her about the issue. She made the correction on the charges and gave me the refund. But I forgot to tell her this was not the first time I was charged for the wrong price. I will keep an eye on the receipts as I don't want to overpay if I shouldn't be. Nobody want to lose money on the high value items. Good Luck!

featured_reviews.review_id:
This is a message for all the kind people concerned about the betta fish:

Don't worry. They're okay. These fish have a very long and difficult trip when they are imported from Asia but are gently cared for when they arrive.
I've spoken with the staff since I had similar concerns and even rescued one of these fish.

Betta will lose color when stressed. It is possible to revive their color within 12 hours (from experience) under suitable conditions.

Their water is changed daily but the lights cause algae to grow rapidly. I experience the same in my planted tank. It's just a natural process.

Yes, some of the fish die and it could be for any reason. They could have been sick prior to capture or perhaps had a rougher trip during import. But I know that the staff do care about them and treat them for disease when and where they can. The fish do not go unnoticed!

I'll post some photos of the fish I saved. The first before/after is only 16 hours apart. You can already see a difference.

Note to staff: please be carefully of moldy food in the betta cups.

While basically all Vets in Canada and especially in BC (including ours), do not recommend them getting tetanus shots. And then PetSmart turns our dog away (1.5 years old) from a grooming session, as his tetanus shot was two weeks out of date. Never getting our business again. What a joke.

featured_reviews.review_id:
One stop shopping, very exciting to visit when you're in love with your pets. Very spacious, clean and well arranged, a lot of foods, treats, toys, clothes, accessories, and other stuffs for your pets. As far as I noticed, they cover dogs off course, cats, fish, birds, reptiles, and other small pets (like rabbits, hamster, guinea pigs, even rats and mice). Although I never used their service, but hard to miss that they also have grooming and training facilities. For the clothes, I found not too many choices, but for food and treats they have quite a lot options to choose. Installing their phone apps is worth it, where we can find promotion info, check stock availability, online shop, book appointment for services, etc.

For Petsmart, keep up the good job!

Perhaps, I have to get another 20 fish next time.

featured_reviews.review_id:
As with any business, some employees are great and some not so great, but the salon staff here are amazing. Ever since Stephanie took over as salon manager, the salon has become SO MUCH BETTER. My dog is reactive and Stephanie is the ONLY one she let's groom her - which she always does an amazing job!

It's obvious that PetSmart as a corporation cares more about money and their customers than it does it's employees, but I can tell that the salon's priority is taking care of the pets and making them feel comfortable. I can't imagine having to deal with reactive dogs and rude customers everyday, but they do an amazing job.

featured_reviews.review_id:
Petsmart...yeah right! More like pet dumb and dumber.  I am NEVER coming back to have my dogs groomed here and I wished I had read the reviews before handing my 4 legged babies over and spending over $880. My dogs and I have been both dramatized, abused and then made wronged for patronizing their business and asking for the services we paid for.   I should of just gone somewhere else as I feel so stupid for being taken as a fool for they basically stole money from us for services they never rendered. When I asked them to do a redo or give me store credit, the staff gang up on you, surround you and then threaten to call the police and escort you out. These staff and Especially that passive aggressive grooming Manager Stephanie to deliver very little for what you pay for and then aggressively verbally attack you to keep the money.

I had to come in with friends in a following visit and video record to recapture Stephanies behaviour and get her name. If this platform allowed video I would just post it and let Stephanie behaviour do all the describing for you.  In conclusion, this business will be going out of business soon if this is how this business operator conducts herself...as a desperate, desperate ghetto trashy individual that is willing to tarnish the reputation of petsmart for the money. Run! Away Do not trust her! As This is an absolutely horrible bully that has to resort to This outright criminal behaviour.

This store is not very busy and pretty quiet, so there should be no reason for the long waits for service or the terrible service. Maybe because they are so horrible, people do not come back and the store is mostly empty of business traffic. Moreover, their inventory is stale and overpriced by 15% to 35%, and their inventory can easily be found on Amazon but a lot cheaper and in better condition. One would also get treated far better down the hill at Bosleys or Tisols.

featured_reviews.review_id:
I usually come in to get to know all the pets before i commit.  These last few visits i noticed that this store is slipping on some very key issues that they really need to improve.

I would rate my last 3 visits as:  Horrible customer service!, rude, and UNsupportive staff members more interested in carrying on in very heated arguments  between themselves or customers with valid complaints. That Groomer named Stephanie is very rude to customers and her co-workers. Staff around her seemed very tired of her abusive & toxic ways. I feel sorry for co-workers. STEPHANIE ONLY CARES ABOUT MONEY, and not how she treats people.  I think this Stephanie brings on the drama with her bad business practices.

I did not enjoy my last 3 visits and just left each time. I do not think i will be buying my next family pet from this store even though I live& work 5 minutes away.  I really felt a review had to be written to prevent any future escalations as it seem it was about to turn violent with all the hostility between dogs and people. I would stay away from this chaotic store.

I recently took my furry companion to PetSmart for a grooming session, and I'm delighted to share my positive experience. The dog grooming service provided by PetSmart was exceptional in every way, from the care given to my pet to the professionalism of the groomers.

Upon arrival, the staff welcomed us with a warm and friendly demeanor, immediately putting my dog at ease. The groomers demonstrated a genuine love for animals and a deep understanding of different breeds and their specific grooming needs.

featured_reviews.review_id: I can responsibly say I've had many pleasant experiences at this store but definitely not today. When I took my dog in for grooming I showed proof of vaccines as I did last time and then two of the staff actually said that my vaccine certificate was invalid. The funny thing is that with this certificate I was able to book my dog in for a training session as well as all the previous grooming services. It's hard not to suspect that they are reducing their workload in this way. The staff have always been friendly and caring perhaps this store is starting to lower their standards. Maybe they shouldn't be called petsmart but staff smart because it's obvious they are missing some smart staff.

featured_reviews.review_id:
Under normal conditions, I would not leave a review. However, the circumstances at Petsmart were so abhorrent that I feel the need to warn consumers. The treatment of the fish is very simply, inexcusable, and the standard of care fails to meet any humane criteria. In many of the tanks, particularly the smaller species such as guppies and tetras, bodies were littering the gravel floor, decorating the waters surface. They were in there for so long, a milky surface had formed on the surface, and white mold surrounded them. Some bodies simply decomposed, the skeleton visible.
In the aquatic fauna section, the leaves that remained either were yellowed and melting away. Some had tiny white dots, a possible sign of disease? There was only one row that was healthy.

I am both horrified and disappointed by Petsmart's treatment of their animals and encourage other buyers to think twice before supporting a business which does not prioritize the wellbeing of animals.

featured_reviews.review_id:
After one hour with the groomer, I received a phone call telling me that they did not have the right equipment to finish the job and did not feel comfortable going forward with my dogs haircut. I understand that he was quite matted and that it wasn't going to be an easy cut. We discussed this beforehand and I asked if he was going to be ok. The groomer checked him out and seemed confident enough. I would have preferred for her to tell me maybe look elsewhere before I handed him over. Instead I was told to book an appointment with a vet or another groomer so they could safely finish my poor boys half trimmed body. I was a little bit in shock as I carried him out to my car with big patches of hair falling off of him. There was no clean up or anything. They just stopped shaving halfway through and essentially gave up. The hard part now is finding a last minute place to take him in fix the mess I was left with.

I did enjoy coming here in the past to get my dogs nails trimmed. But after todays grooming experience, I will not be heading back.
